<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/287: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-05T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 5,
                                            1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Strictly confidential. In your opinion is will of majority of people
                                of Peru expressed in support of action of Leguia in overthrowing
                                Pardo and calling for new elections. Give Department available
                                figures for Leguia and figures for Government candidate in recent
                                election.</p>
                            <p>Have you discovered any tangible proofs of plot to defraud Leguia.
                                Cable reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>